erves deploy partial non-spin. 2,500 |\n| Testing | Annual 30 minute test. | | Annual 30 minute test. | | Annual 30 minute test. |\n| Value | $50/MW-year | $50-$100k/MW-year | | avg depending on price and proration | Averaging $91k/MW year since increase procurement in July 2021. Historically averaged between $25k/MW |\n| Proration | No, but increased participation leads to decreased pricing. | Yes, currently averaging between 65%-85% MW awarded. | | | Potentially if significant MW of LR/NSRS participate. |\n| Consequence | Decreased Payment. Potential PUC fines. | Potential SASM opened up in Real-Time. Potential PUC fines. | | | Potential SASM opened up in Real-Time. Potential PUC |\n| Event? | No | | | Yes | Yes |\n\n| Parameter Emergency Response Service | Load Resource (RRS) | | | Non-Spinning Reserves | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Notification Window 10 & 30 minute options | 10 minute or instantaneous UFR trip | | | | 30 minute |\n| | | | Enrollment any time throughout the | Offer into day-ahead market. | year. |\n| 15 minute utility interval meter Requirements | 2 second telemetry with UFR requirement | | 2 second telemetry | | without UFR requirement |\n| | | 2021: 7 days of events in Feb. 2 events in | 2.5 hrs. 2 events in | 2019: 2 events for 2020: 1 event for 4.5 hours. | avg 2 hours. April for avg June for avg 3.5 hours. |\n| | EEA 2 (1,750 MW reserves) or UFR trip at 59.7 Hz for 20 | Varying conditions and can be deployed at ERCOT discre tion. (3,200 MW reserves deploy partial non-spin. 2,500 | | MW reserves deploy all non-spin.) | |\n| Testing Annual 30 minute test. | Annual 30 minute test. | | | Annual 30 minute test. | |\n| Value $50/MW-year | $50-$100k/MW-year avg depending on price and proration | Averaging $91k/MW in July 2021. Historically averaged between $25k/MW | | year and $135k/MW-year. | year since increase procurement |\n| Proration No, but increased participation leads to decreased pricing. | Yes, currently averaging betwee